    DoubleRect
    Java class to simulate a QuickDraw Rect (rectangle) with double coordinates In Pascal, a QuickDraw Rect is defined this way: TYPE RECT = RECORD (left, top, right, bottom: INTEGER); The bounding box calculations in Classic Watchmaker use a Pascal Rect record, which is defined by left, top, right, and bottom coordinates.
